main event: A UFO was reportedly observed in the sky over Richardson, Texas on April 18, 1965.
interesting points: The object was whitish-silver in color and approximately 40-50 feet in length.
The object appeared to hover briefly, then dropped about 100 feet before accelerating to a very high speed, estimated to be several hundred miles per hour.
The object was observed by multiple witnesses who stated it was not a satellite, aircraft, or any other conventional man-made object.
Another report was filed on June 2, 1966 by a witness in Richardson who observed two silent, disc-shaped objects that moved in an unusual manner.
The Air Force's Foreign Technology Division requested additional information from the witnesses to complete their investigation.
result: Inconclusive - insufficient data for positive identification
photographs: No photographs present in the provided documentation
